Interface ITerminologyBrowser<C,K>

  • Type Parameters:
    C - the concept type
    K - the concept unique identifier type
    All Superinterfaces:
    ExtendedComponentProvider, SuperTypeIdProvider<K>

    public interface ITerminologyBrowser<C,K>
extends ExtendedComponentProvider, SuperTypeIdProvider<K>
    Interface for browsing a hierarchy of concepts on the server side.

      • exists

        boolean exists(IBranchPath branchPath,
               String componentId)
        Checks whether a component identified by its terminology specific unique ID exits on the given branch. Returns with true if the component exists, otherwise returns with false.
        Parameters:
        branchPath - the branch path identifying the branch to check the existence.
        componentId - the terminology specific unique ID.

      • exist

        Map<String,Boolean> exist(IBranchPath branchPath,
                          Collection<String> componentIds)
        Checks whether the components identified by their terminology specific unique IDs exist on the given branch. Returns with a map, where the keys are the component IDs and the values are true or false whether the component exists or not.
        Parameters:
        branchPath - the branch path identifying the branch to check the existence.
        componentIds - the terminology specific unique IDs.
        Returns:
        map where each ID is mapped to true or false whether it exists or not.
